gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 96, Nets 94
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Nets, 96-94. Karl-Anthony Towns recorded a game-high 27 points, along with 10 rebounds and three assists, while Anthony Edwards added 24 points and three assists in the victory. Cam Thomas tallied 25 points and six rebounds for the Nets in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 32-13 on the season, while the Nets fall to 17-27.
